    """
    
    story = """
Once upon a time in a small village in India, there lived a young boy named Arun.
Arun was known for his cleverness, but he sometimes chose easy shortcuts instead of telling the truth.

One day, Arun found a purse filled with coins near the village temple.
He thought about keeping it, but his heart reminded him of the importance of honesty.
Arun decided to take the purse to the village elder.

The elder smiled and praised Arun for his honesty.
The villagers respected Arun even more, and he felt proud of doing the right thing.

Moral of the Story:
